---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="Weather Abroad: Quick Celsius to Fahrenheit for Travellers" description="Quick Celsius/Fahrenheit reference for travellers. Understand weather forecasts abroad and know what to wear instantly." keywords="celsius to fahrenheit weather, travel temperature, weather conversion, celsius weather guide, fahrenheit abroad, temperature for travellers, weather forecast units">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Temperature</span>
      </nav>
      <BlogCrossLinks title="Weather Abroad: Quick Celsius to Fahrenheit for Travellers" />
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">June 21, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>You check the weather at your holiday destination and it says 28°C. Is that hot? Cold? Do you need a jacket? If you grew up with Fahrenheit, Celsius weather forecasts can feel meaningless. Here is a practical guide to interpreting temperatures abroad.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Weather Temperature Ranges</h2>
      <p>Rather than memorising exact conversions, learn these ranges:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Below 0°C (32°F):</strong> Freezing — ice, snow, heavy winter gear</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>0-10°C (32-50°F):</strong> Cold — winter coat, layers, gloves</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>10-15°C (50-59°F):</strong> Cool — jacket or sweater weather</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>15-20°C (59-68°F):</strong> Mild — light layers, comfortable</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>20-25°C (68-77°F):</strong> Warm — t-shirt weather, pleasant</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>25-30°C (77-86°F):</strong> Hot — summer clothing, sunscreen</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>30-35°C (86-95°F):</strong> Very hot — seek shade, stay hydrated</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>35°C+ (95°F+):</strong> Extreme heat — limit outdoor activity</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Quick Mental Conversion Trick</h2>
      <p>For a rough estimate when you are out and about:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Double the Celsius number</li>
        <li>Add 30</li>
      </ol>
      <p>This gets you within a few degrees:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>10°C: (10 × 2) + 30 = 50°F (actual: 50°F — perfect)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>20°C: (20 × 2) + 30 = 70°F (actual: 68°F — close enough)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>30°C: (30 × 2) + 30 = 90°F (actual: 86°F — close)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">City Weather in Context</h2>
      <p>Popular destinations and their typical summer/winter temperatures:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>London:</strong> Winter 5°C (41°F), Summer 22°C (72°F)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Paris:</strong> Winter 4°C (39°F), Summer 25°C (77°F)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Tokyo:</strong> Winter 5°C (41°F), Summer 30°C (86°F)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Dubai:</strong> Winter 19°C (66°F), Summer 42°C (108°F)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Sydney:</strong> Winter 13°C (55°F), Summer 26°C (79°F)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Bangkok:</strong> Year-round 28-35°C (82-95°F)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Packing Tips Based on Temperature</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Below 10°C:</strong> Pack thermal base layers, insulated jacket, scarf, warm socks</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>10-20°C:</strong> Layers work best — cardigan plus a light waterproof jacket</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>20-30°C:</strong> Light fabrics, shorts, sunglasses, sunscreen, hat</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Above 30°C:</strong> Loose linen or cotton, wide-brimmed hat, water bottle</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>When in doubt, check both the daytime high and overnight low at your destination. Many places have a 10-15°C swing between day and night.</p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/convert/temperature" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Temperature Converter →</a>
      </div>
    
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our converter: <a href="/convert/temperature" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold hover:underline">Open Converter →</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
